are they confronting?

00:23:08.200 --> 00:23:10.750
And what they are confronting is

00:23:10.750 --> 00:23:13.770
a paradigm that lets black people

00:23:13.770 --> 00:23:15.030
get killed in their own homes, right?

00:23:15.030 --> 00:23:17.870
And even though that
posture is confrontational

00:23:17.870 --> 00:23:21.250
to something, different
audiences read that differently.

00:23:21.250 --> 00:23:22.520
So when we were walking through that

00:23:22.520 --> 00:23:23.670
working class black community,

00:23:23.670 --> 00:23:25.120
it doesn't feel confrontational.

00:23:25.120 --> 00:23:27.430
